1st normal form
--------
2 rules
1. no repeating groups
2. every row should be unique

each cell to be single valued
entries in a column are same type
rows uniquly identified = add unique id, or add more columns to make unique
order of rows and columns irrelevant

no multivalued fields
each table has a unique identifier called a primary key


2nd normal form
---------
must be in 1nf
no partial key dependancies
all attributes must be dependant on the key

every non-prime attribute is dependant exclusivelt on the primary key


3rd normal form
----------
must be in 1nf and 2nf
attributes must be dependant solely on the key

all fields(columns) can be determined only by the key in the table and no other column

attributes are determined only by the primary key